A pedestrian was killed and three other people were injured in a car crash on the corner of Delfos Boulevard and the Golden Highway in Vanderbijlpark in Southern Gauteng on Sunday morning, paramedics said.
When ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene shortly after 9am they found three patients sitting in front of a vehicle. All three had sustained minor injuries, ER24 spokesperson Ineke van Huyssteen said.
“A pedestrian was found a few metres away and had sustained fatal injuries. The patient was declared dead on the scene by paramedics. ER24 transported the patients to hospital for further medical care.”
The cause of the accident was not yet known, Van Huyssteen said.
– African News Agency (ANA)
